15 (1) 'Agency' means the State of Georgia and any branch, department, agency, division,
16 board, bureau, entity, official, employee, or agent of the state and any county,
17 municipality, school district, consolidated government, or authority created by or
18 pursuant to the Constitution of the State of Georgia or any general or local law of this
19 state and any official, employee, or agent of any such entity.
20 (2) 'Artificial intelligence system' means an engineered or machine based system that
21 emulates the capability of a person to receive audio, visual, text, or any other form of
22 information and use the information received to emulate a human cognitive process,
23 including, but not limited to, learning, generalizing, reasoning, planning, predicting,
24 acting, or communicating; provided, however, that artificial intelligence systems may
25 vary in the forms of information they can receive and in the human cognitive processes
26 they can emulate.
27 50-29-31.
28 No agency shall install or use any artificial intelligence system on state equipment if the
29 company that developed or deployed such artificial intelligence system is directly or
30 indirectly owned or operated by the People's Republic of China or is domiciled in, has its
31 principal place of business in, has headquarters in, or is organized under the laws of the
32 People's Republic of China."
33 SECTION 2.
34 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
